AGI - The helicopter on which the Iranian President Ebrahim Rais traveled,&nbsp;>assieme to other people,&nbsp; was forced to an emergency landing in Azerbaijan. The fate of the occupants of the aircraft, whose finding - initially reported by Iranian television - was denied by the Red Crescent, although the area of the incident was identified, where the &nbsp was headed by the Guardians of the Islamic Revolution, Hossein Salami>, who took part in an emergency meeting on crisis management. The Tasnim agency reports it. Other Pasdaran commanders, local officials and authorities participated in the meeting.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Raisi also traveled Aytollah Al-Hashem, Imam of Juma Tabriz, Foreign Minister Hossein Amirabdollahian, Governor of Azerbaijan Oriental Malik Rahmati and many others, reports the information body. The difficult weather conditions, the rain, the thick fog and the arrival of the dark are complicating the work of rescue teams even if, as reportedly &nbsp;vice President Mohsen Mansouri, quoted by Irna (the printing agency of the Islamic Republic), rescuers would establish a contact > with at least two passengers.&nbsp;Raisi was back from the opening of a dam on Iran.
&nbsp;
"The lives of President Raisi and Foreign Minister Amirabdollahian are at risk > following the helicopter crash," said an Iranian official at Reuters, adding: "We are still confident, but the information from the place of the accident is very worrying." Twenty rescue teams are at work to find the helicopter. The research, said Interior Minister Ahmed Vahidi on state television, is very difficult because of the "favourable weather conditions", and in particular a thick fog. "It could take time to reach the area," he added, although it is believed that the place is in the forest of Dizmar, near the town of Varzaghan.&nbsp; A helicopter that had to look for the crash site was forced to go back.
&nbsp;
The Iranian Supreme Guide, the Aytollah Ali Khamenei>, held an urgent meeting with the country's Security Council after the incident news.&nbsp; The official agency Irna, which mentions the spokesman of the government Ali Bahadri Jahormi, writes that after the emergency meeting of the government council in Tehran, the executive vice president and some members of the Iranian government left for Tabriz, near the place where the apparatus with on board the president would end his flight.
&nbsp;
"We hope that God will bring back the honorable president and his companions in the arms of the nation. Everyone should pray for the health of this group of servants. If the Iranian people do not care, there will be no interruptions in the work of the country," said Khamenei during a meeting with the Pasdaran families.

